revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Floor_LowerToNearest}} {{Special|22|tag, speed|Floor|LowerToNearest}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How quickly the floor moves
Lowers a tagged sector's floor to the height of the highest surrounding floor that is lower than the tagged sector's current height. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.
== Examples ==
{{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Floor_LowerToNearest: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Boom}} 219:W1 Floor Down To Adjacent Floor || Floor_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Boom}} 220:WR Floor Down To Adjacent Floor || Floor_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 221:S1 Floor Down To Adjacent Floor || Floor_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 222:SR Floor Down To Adjacent Floor || Floor_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|F_SLOW}}) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
